{{Quote|Alderaanians are about to ''die''. It would be nice if they did so knowing their princess ''gives'' a damn. I must say ''something'' ''[&hellip;]'' ''"<br />"''You already ''know'' what to ''say'', Leia. Have you even ''noticed'' that I've stopped addressing you formally? No "''ma'am''"? No "''your highness''"? I did it because you threw everything away for ''Tula''. That reminded me of all your ''other'' sacrifices, and those made me think of your ''achievements''.|Princess Leia Organa and Evaan Verlaine|<ref name="Leia 5">[[Princess Leia 5|''Princess Leia'' 5]]</ref>}}
A '''princess''' was a member of a [[noble]] family.<ref name="Databank Leia Organa" /> "[[Prince]]" was a typically [[Gender|masculine]] equivalent of "princess."

==History==
Princess [[Sicatra]] of [[Bethune]] and Prince [[Colden]] of [[Firevale]] were partly responsible for a bloody [[Siege of Firevale|battle]] between their peoples during the [[High Republic Era]].<ref name="Blade 4">[[The High Republic — The Blade 4|''The High Republic — The Blade'' 4]]</ref> The [[Jedi]] [[Rael Averross]] served as the [[Regent|lord regent]] of [[Pijal]] for Princess [[Fanry]].<ref name="M&A">''[[Master & Apprentice]]''</ref> [[Roola]] was a [[Hutt]] princess who ruled the [[moon]]s of [[Syvris]] before she was kidnapped by the Hutt [[gangster]] [[Pashda]], who had been contracted by the [[Mon Calamari]] [[Basz]].<ref name="Knights of Fate">''[[Knights of Fate]]''</ref>

Although she was the daughter of a defrocked [[Jedi Knight]] and a [[senator]]<ref name="Databank Leia Organa" /> of humble origins,<ref name="DB-Leia-bio">{{Databank|leia-organa-biography-gallery|Leia Organa}} {{C|Image 1}}</ref> [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia Organa]] became a princess following her adoption into the [[House of Organa|Royal Family]] of [[Alderaan]]. She was referred to by her title alongside her first name, as Princess Leia,<ref name="Databank Leia Organa" /> and formally addressed as "your highness" in the first instance and then as "ma'am" by those who recognized her as a princess of her own right<ref name="Leia 5" />&mdash;including during her time in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] after the [[Galactic Empire]] [[Destruction of Alderaan|destroyed]] Alderaan.<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref> If not for the destruction of Organa's adopted [[homeworld]], her son [[Ben Solo]] would have been born as the Prince of Alderaan.<ref name="Skywalker: A Family at War">''[[Skywalker: A Family at War]]''</ref>

During the Rebellion's [[Galactic Civil War|war]] against the Empire, Princess Leia and fellow Alderaanian [[Evaan Verlaine]] [[Mission to rescue the survivors of Alderaan|rescued]] Alderaan's survivors. As the [[Alderaan Flotilla]] hid from the Empire, Princess Leia continued serving as a commander in the Rebellion but endorsed Verlaine to stand for a fair election as Alderaan's princess.<ref name="Leia 5" /> In later [[Standard year|years]], Organa would eschew the title of princess in favor of the role of [[general]] in the [[Resistance]] against the [[First Order]], allowing only her close friends to use the title.<ref name="TFA">{{Film|VII}}</ref> In fact, the title no longer carried much [[Politics|political]] weight in a [[New Republic]] determined to uphold [[Democracy|democratic]] ideals.<ref name="awakensvisual">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref>

